getAttributeValue

public static java.lang.Object getAttributeValue(DeployModelObject dmo,
                                                 java.lang.String attributeName)
Returns the value of the static or dynamic deploy model object attribute.

Deploy model objects have static EMF attributes defined in DeployModelObject#eClass() and dynamic attributes defined in DeployModelObject.getExtendedAttributes(). This method first attempts to resolve the attribute name as a static attribute, and then as a dynamic one.

The method returns null if an attribute is not defined as either static or dynamic. To find out if an attribute has been defined use hasAttribute(DeployModelObject, String).

The attribute name make be local, or relative to the deploy object. For example, if the attribute name was created using getFullPathToAttribute(DeployModelObject, EAttribute) then the dmo object will be used to DeployModelObject.resolve(String), and then the attribute will be retrieved from the specified object. In such cases, the dmo parameter to this method will typically be a Topology instance.

Parameters:
dmo -
attributeName - the name of a static or dynamic attribute: local or contextual (embedding a DeployModelObject.getFullPath()).
Returns:
the attribute value or null if the attribute is defined. To find out if an attribute is defined use hasAttribute(DeployModelObject, String).
See Also:
hasAttribute(DeployModelObject, String)
